goals.question: What is the distribution of car prices?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of car prices in the dataset and identify any outliers.

code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

# read data
data = pd.read_json('cars.json')

# plot histogram of car prices
plt.hist(data['price'], bins=20, color='blue')
plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Price: {:.2f}'.format(data['price'].mean()))
plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Price: {:.2f}'.format(data['price'].median()))
plt.xlabel('Price')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.title('What is the distribution of car prices?')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['engine-size'], data['price'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Engine Size')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.axvline(data['engine-size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', label='Median Engine Size: {:.2f}'.format(data['engine-size'].median()))
    plt.axhline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', label='Median Price: {:.2f}'.format(data['price'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the relationship between car price and engine size?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

# read data
data = pd.read_json('cars.json')

# plot histogram of car mileage
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
ax.hist(data['mileage'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
ax.axvline(data['mileage'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
ax.axvline(data['mileage'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
ax.set_xlabel('Mileage')
ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
ax.set_title('What is the distribution of car mileage?')
ax.legend()

plt.show()
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
```

```
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    make_counts = data['make'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(make_counts.index, make_counts.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Car Make')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of car make?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
